&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Newham University Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acute and Emergency Medicine &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Matron for Acute Admissions Unit &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following a recent restructuring of the Medicine division, an exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced senior nurse to join the newly established Acute Admissions Unit as Matron.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an exceptional nurse leader who will be a key part of the acute medicine leadership team with oversight and responsibility for the Acute Admissions Unit. The unit has 52 beds and accepts direct admissions from our Emergency Department for all specialties including patients requiring cardiac monitoring.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported by the Senior Nurse; and work with a team of ward managers, practice development nurse to drive forward improvements and continue to raise standards and quality within the division.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a candidate who is clinically focused and visible but also able to work in a leadership role with the clinical leads and service managers to develop the unit further within their remit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of Barts Health there is also a wealth of training and development opportunities available to the successful applicant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome informal visits. To arrange a visit or for a discussion, please contact Ferenc Habermann, Senior nurse for Acute Medicine on f.habermann@nhs.net or Andrea McDonnell, Associate Director of Nursing via andrea.mcdonnell1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAndrea McDonnellJob titleAssociate Director of NursingEmail addressandrea.mcdonnell1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
